name: Pentagon 001
description:
In the past, we clearly felt the line between simulation and reality when playing ZX Spectrum. The line is now being erased. We look at these 100 faces on NFT, and see people, although they never existed (these are the faces of non-existent people from Thispersondoesnotexist). The question arises: at what point do we stop distinguishing our old physical life from the new life in the simulation?

1080x1080 MPEG-4
